\fs24\b Project: Skills International School Management System\b0\par
\par
\b 1. Project Overview\b0\par
This document describes the deliverables required for the project, provides GUI and database design guidance, code snippets to connect the system to SQL Server, and a submission checklist. Include screenshots of each form and code snippets in the final Microsoft Word submission.
\par
\b 2. Requirements (from instructor)\b0\par
1. Design the software system according to the given instructions.\par
2. Use appropriate fonts, colors, and images for Frontend (GUI design).\par
3. System must have a database and be properly connected (SQL Server).\par
4. Database must contain at least one table (see sample structure below).\par
5. Test the software and submit before the deadline.\par
6. Create a Microsoft Word Document including screenshots of forms and code snippets.\par
7. Include full project brief in the document.
\par
\b 3. GUI Design Guidance\b0\par
- Recommended fonts: "Segoe UI" (UI), "Arial" (fallback).\par
- Sizes: Labels 10-12pt, Inputs 10-12pt, Form title 14-16pt.\par
- Colors: Use a neutral background (e.g., #F5F7FA), primary accent (e.g., #2B6CB0 - blue), success (#2F855A - green), error (#E53E3E - red).\par
- Images: Use school logo at top-left of main forms (PNG with transparency).\par
- Accessibility: Ensure contrast ratio and keyboard navigation for controls.
\par
\b 4. Database Design (SQL Server)\b0\par
- Use SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) to create the database (example name: `SkillsDB`).\par
- Example table: `Students` (this is the "minimum one table" required).\par
\b SQL script to create table:\b0\par
\f1\fs20
CREATE TABLE Students (\par
    Id INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,\par
    AdmissionNo VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL UNIQUE,\par
    FirstName NVARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,\par
    LastName NVARCHAR(100) NULL,\par
    DOB DATE NULL,\par
    Gender VARCHAR(10) NULL,\par
    Class VARCHAR(50) NULL,\par
    Email VARCHAR(100) NULL,\par
    Phone VARCHAR(20) NULL,\par
    Address NVARCHAR(255) NULL,\par
    CreatedAt DATETIME DEFAULT GETDATE()\par
);\par
\f0\fs24
\par
\b Connection string examples (for .NET Framework 4.7.2)\b0\par
- Windows Authentication:\par
`Data Source=SERVERNAME;Initial Catalog=SkillsDB;Integrated Security=True;`\par
- SQL Server Authentication:\par
`Data Source=SERVERNAME;Initial Catalog=SkillsDB;User ID=sa;Password=YourPassword;`\par
\par
\b 5. C# code snippets\b0\par
\f1\fs20
